s28", "video_description": "Imagine a game played with two players and two dice: if the biggest number rolled is one, two, three, or four, player 1 wins. If the biggest number rolled is five or six, player 2 wins. Who has the best probability of winning the game? Leonardo Barichello explains how probability holds the answer to this seemingly counterintuitive puzzle.", "video_link": "https://ed.ted.com/lessons/the-last-banana-a-thought-experiment-in-probability-leonardo-barichello", "video_title_length": "The last banana: A thought experiment in probability - Leonardo Barichello - 04:10"}